Service is quick and the food is delicious.
I frequent this place for lunch.
The burritos tend to be a little on the sloppy side, but that's just because they're incredibly juicy and extremely packed inside, so I'm certainly not complaining about it.
Biggest tip: There is a small cart on the back wall with many side items that you can place into provided baggies.
I *highly* recommend the spicy carrots.
No extra charge!

